Running around uptown with @nikewomen ⭐️👟

I’m an LA girl who grew up coming to Harlem year after year, so inevitably my personal style also grew with the cultures of both coasts. Nike has always been a part of that reality in one way or another, from tennis practice in the valley to getting my first pair of AF1s at the footlocker on 125th lol <3 #TeamNike #NikeIRL

I attended my 1st nude dinner the night before last and it was such a fun and relaxing time!!

The evening opened with guided meditation through the 5 elements in traditional Chinese herbalism, followed by a 3 course plant based dinner, and open conversation. 

It got me thinking so much about clothing and what we say with our clothes, whether that be the music we listen to, the amount of money we make, the people we look up to, etc. We signal so much through clothing. When all that is stripped away, you’re simply a person (also super cool being able to see everyone’s tattoos!!)

There was a safety coordinator present and everyone there was thoroughly vetted by Charlie, who hosted the experience. At a certain point in the evening I kind of forgot that everyone was naked, you’re just having conversation and looking people in the eye like you would at any other dinner/event. But there’s a deeper sense of intimacy and awareness for each other and yourself. 

Thank u a million 2 Charlie and everyone involved in putting this dreamscape together 🤍🤍🤍 here’s to desexualizing the natural form and existing comfortably within our vessels!!
